full_entry: अंक aṅka m. 1. number. 2. issue (of a magazine, newspaper). 3. act (of a play).

कर kara m. tax. ० बसवणे to tax. ० भरणे , देणे to pay tax. m., f., n. suff. of -- (place), e. g., नगर 0 `of Nagar', पुणे 0 `of Poona.' When a family moves to another town this designation often becomes a surname. m. suff. agentive suff. e. g., विण 0 weaver.
करकचणे karakacaṇē v.t. to bind tightly. Generally used with a following verb, e. g., करकचून बांधणे v.i. to tense.
करकोचा karakōcā m. 1. crane. 2. mark left on the body by tight clothing.
करंगळी karaṅgaḷī f. little finger or little toe.
करंडा karaṇḍā m. 1. large deep basket. 2. small container, usually metal (as for vermillion powder).
करडे karaḍē adj. 1. iron gray. 2. stern.
करण karaṇa n.suff. abstract noun-making suff. meaning `making.' Of. Eng. -- ization, -- ification, e. g., औद्योगी industrialization, राष्ट्रीयी 0 nationalization.
करणे karaṇē v.t. (irreg.) 1. to do. 2. to make. 3. to grow.
करता karatā post. in order to, for the purpose of.
करपणे karapaṇē v.i. to be burned.
करमणे karamaṇē v.i. (N-la impers.) to pass time pleasantly without getting bored.
कर्कश karkaśa adj. inv. harsh, grating.
कर्ज karja n. debt, loan. ० घेणे , काढणे to take a loan. ० देणे to give a loan.
कर्णधार karṇadhāra m. chief, captain (of a team).
कर्तरी kartarī , प्रयोग prayōga a sentence construction in which the verb agrees with the agent.
कर्ता kartā m. 1. agent. 2. household head. 3. (gram.) subject.
कर्तृत्व kartṛtva n. power of doing, achievement.
कर्म karma n. 1. action. 2. (gram.) object. 3. exasperated expletive.
कर्मठ karmaṭha adj. inv. strict in adherence to religious ritual, orthodox.
कर्मणी karmaṇī , प्रयोग prayōga a sentence construction in which the verb agrees with the object.
कर्मयोग karmayōga m. the way to salvation through action rather than renunciation.
कलंक kalaṅka m. stigma, blot. ० लावणे to give a bad name, be a blot.
कलंडणे kalaṇḍaṇē v.i. 1. to tip. 2. to lie down.
कलणे kalaṇē v.i. to lean, begin to decline.
कलम kalama n. 1. section, clause. 2. pen. 3. cutting off, amputation. 4. graft.
कलमी kalamī adj. inv. grafted. Used loosely to refer to any improved variety of fruit.
कलाकृती kalākṛtī f. work of art.
कल्पना kalpanā f. 1. idea. 2. power of imagination. ० करणे to imagine.
कल्लोळ kallōḷa m. turbulence, tumultuous noise.
कल्हई kalhaī f. a coating of tin given to brass utensils.
कवच kavaca n. 1. hard shell. 2. armor.
कवळी kavaḷī f. set of teeth (now used esp. to refer to false teeth).
कविता kavitā f. poetry, poem. ० करणे , लिहिणे to write poetry.
कशा kaśā obl. form of कसे .
कष्ट kaṣṭa m.pl. 1. hard work. ० करणे to work hard. 2. distress. ० होणे to be in distress.
कंस kaṃsa m. 1. segment of a circle. 2. bracket.
कसदार kasadāra adj. inv. 1. of good quality. 2. nutritious. 3. fertile.
कसर kasara f.(i) 1. moth. 2. deficiency, shortfall.
कसाई kasāī m. a Muslim butcher.
कसूर kasūra m., f. negligence, fault.
कसे kasē adv. how. ० दिले ? How much does it cost ? (lit., How given ?).
कसेबसे kasēbasē adv. var. somehow, with difficulty.
कसोटी kasōṭī f. test. ० घेणे to give a test. ० लावणे to apply a test. ० ला उतरणे to meet a test.
कहर kahara m. the limit, excess.
कहाणी kahāṇī f. story (esp. one of a body of women's stories teaching the importance of certain religious observances.)
कळ kaḷa f.(i) 1. sharp pain. 2. gadget. 3. quarrelling. ० लावणे to incite a quarrel.
कळणे kaḷaṇē v.i. (N-la impers.) to know, come to know, realize, understand.
कळवळणे kaḷavaḷaṇē v.i. 1. to be moved with pity. 2. to suffer, agonize.
कळशी kaḷaśī f. small narrow-necked metal water pot.
कळस kaḷasa m. pinnacle, height. ० होणे to reach a crisis.
कळावे kaḷāvē May you understand. (Formal close of letter.)
का kā particle used to form yes-no questions. adv. why.
का kā , कू kū , करणे karaṇē to hesitate.
काका kākā m. father's brother (term of reference and address.)
काकू kākū f. father's brother's wife (term of reference and address.) Frequently used for any matronly woman.
कागद kāgada m. 1. paper, sheet of paper. 2. legal document.
कांगाव kāṅgāva m. whining for an inconsequential reason.
कागाळी kāgāḷī f. complaint, informing against.
काच kāca f.(e) glass, piece of glass.
काचणे kācaṇē v.i. (N-la impers.) to bite (as a tight cord bites into the skin).
कांचन kāñcana n. gold. m. bauhinia, a flowering tree.
काचा kācā m. tuck. ० मारणे . to tuck up.
काजळी kājaḷī f. soot, lamp black.
काटणे kāṭaṇē v.t. 1. to traverse. 2. to cut (cards). 3. to cut out, omit.
काटा kāṭā m. 1. thorn. 2. fork. 3. weighing scale. 4. goosepimples. अंगावर ० उभा राहणे to get goosepimples. 5. hand of a clock or watch, indicator.
काटेकोर kāṭēkōra adj. inv. exact, accurate.
काठोकाठ kāṭhōkāṭha adv. up to the brim.
कांडणे kāṇḍaṇē v.t. to pound in a mortar.
काडी kāḍī f. 1. small stick, twig. 2. blade (as of grass). 3. matchstick.
कांडी kāṇḍī f. 1. short stick, wand. 2. cutting (of a plant).
काढणे kāḍhaṇē v.t. 1. to pull, draw out, take out. काढून घेणे to take away. 2. to grow (a crop). 3. to harvest. 4. to let out (a sound). 5. to draw (a picture). 6. to borrow (money).
काढा kāḍhā m. a decoction of medicinal herbs.
कात kāta f.(i) 1. skin (esp. of a snake). ० टाकणे to shed a skin. m. catechu (an ingredient of पान ).
कातरणे kātaraṇē v.t. to cut with scissors.
काथ्या kāthyā m. coir, coir rope.
कान kāna m. ear. As in Eng. this is also used to refer to the ear of a cup. ० देणे to listen. कानावर पडणे to hear.
कानडी kānaḍī adj. inv. belonging to Karnataka (Mysore). n. Kannada (Kanarese) language.
काना kānā m. the vertical line used in the Devanagari script for some of the vowel signs.
कानाडोळा kānāḍōḷā , करणे karaṇē to wink at, overlook.
कापड kāpaḍa n. a piece of cloth, cloth.
कापणे kāpaṇē v.t. 1. to cut. 2. to traverse. v.i. to shake, tremble.
कापरे kāparē adj. shaky. n. tremor, trembling.
काबीज kābīja , करणे karaṇē to seize, take over.
काबूत kābūta , येणे yēṇē to come within the control of.
काम kāma n. 1. work. कामाला or कामावर जाणे to go to work. 2. role (as in a play). m. sexual desire.
कामचलाऊ kāmacalāū adj. inv. passable, barely serviceable.
कायम kāyama adv. permanently. adj. inv. permanent.
कार kāra m. suff. agentive suff., e.g., कला 0 artist.
कारक kāraka adj. suff. inv. adjective-making suff. indicating agency.
कारकीर्द kārakīrda f.(i) reign, rule, period of authority.
कारण kāraṇa n. cause, reason. conj. because.
कारणीभूत kāraṇībhūta adj. inv. causative. ० होणे to be the cause of.
कारभार kārabhāra m. 1. administration. 2. undesirable action.
कारवाई kāravāī f. 1. action. 2. scheme. ० करणे to take action.
कारुण्य kāruṇya n. 1. compassion. 2. tragic quality.
कार्टा kārṭā m. (in pl. n.) brat.
कार्य kārya n. 1. task, work. Usually refers to work of greater significance than does काम 2. rite of passage.
कार्यक्रम kāryakrama m. schedule of work, program.
काल kāla adv. yesterday. See also काळ .
कालवण kālavaṇa n. any preparation of vegetables or meat.
कावकाव kāvakāva f. 1. the cawing of crows. 2. noise, racket.
कावेबाज kāvēbāja adj. inv. cunning. wily.
कासरा kāsarā m. rope used as a rein for a bullock.
कासार kāsāra m. merchant dealing in pots, pans and glass bangles.
कासोटा kāsōṭā m. the tuck made when the front folds of the sari or dhoti are passed between the legs and brought up in the back.
काही kāhī adj. inv. some, any.
काहीबाही kāhībāhī something bad or inauspicious.
काहील kāhīla f.(i) shallow iron pan.
काळजी kāḷajī f. 1. anxiety, worry. care. ० करणे , वाटणे to worry. 2. solicitude. ० घेणे to take pains, care for.
काळिमा kāḷimā m. stain, blot. ० लावणे to give a bad name, be a blot, blacken.
काळीज kāḷīja n. 1. liver. 2. seat of the emotions (equivalent to Eng. `heart').
किचकट kicakaṭa adj. inv. minute, complicated.
किंचित kiñcita adv. a little, somewhat.
किटणे kiṭaṇē v.i. to be fed up with. आवाजाने कान 0 to be fed up with a noise.
किडकिडीत kiḍakiḍīta adj. inv. thin, lean.
किडणे kiḍaṇē v.i. to be wormeaten, decay.
कितपत kitapata adv. how much, to what extent.
कितवे kitavē adj. which (regarding position in a series). कितवी which grade.
किती kitī inv. how much, how many. ० वाजता at what time.
कितीदा kitīdā adv. how many times.
किंबहुना kimbahunā adv. what's more, nay, not merely that but.
किमान kimāna adv. at least. adj. inv. minimum.
किरकिर kirakira f.(i) peevish complaining, whining.
किरकोळ kirakōḷa adj. inv. 1. slim, slender. 2. trivial, petty. 3. miscellaneous. adv. by retail, in small quantities.
किराणा kirāṇā m. groceries (excluding fresh produce.)
किलबिल kilabila f.(i) chatter of birds.
की kī adv. then. conj. or. Emphatic particle, e. g., या की do come.
कीड kīḍa f.(i) insect, worm, maggot. ० लागणे , पडणे to be attacked by insects.
कीर्तन kīrtana n. religious discourse accompanied by bhajan.
कीर्तनकार kīrtanakāra m. performer of kirtans.
कीव kīva f.(e) pity. ० येणे , करणे to pity.
कीस kīsa m. gratings, scrapings. ० काढणे to make fine distinctions.
कु ku pref. negative pref. often meaning `bad.'
कु ku abbrev. of कुमार or कुमारी .
कुंकू kuṅkū n. vermillion powder. This is traditionally worn on the forehead by married women whose husbands are living. It is now worn by any woman.
कुचंबणा kucambaṇā f. restraint, difficult position.
कुजके kujakē adj. 1. rotten. 2. malicious, slanderous.
कुटणे kuṭaṇē v.t. to pound with a mortar and pestle.
कुटिल kuṭila adj. inv. crooked, devious, hateful.
कुटुंब kuṭumba n. 1. family. 2. (old-fashioned usage) wife.
कुठले kuṭhalē adj. from where, which, what sort.
कुठले kuṭhalē , तरी tarī adj. some.
कुठवर kuṭhavara adv. how far, how long.
कुंड kuṇḍa n. pool of water.
कुडकुडणे kuḍakuḍaṇē v.i. to shiver (with cold).
कुडते kuḍatē n. shirt, piece of clothing.
कुडी kuḍī f. 1. clove (as of garlic). 2. body. 3. earstud.
कुंडी kuṇḍī f. an earthen pot used for small plants.
कुढणे kuḍhaṇē v.i. to mope, fret.
कुणकुण kuṇakuṇa f.(i) whisper, rumor. ० लागणे to hear a rumor.
कुणबी kuṇabī m. 1. cultivator. 2. a community of cultivators and agricultural laborers which has now become assimilated among the Maratha castes.
कुणी kuṇī pron. 1. someone. 2. instr. of कोण .
कुत्सित kutsita adj. inv. contemptuous, sarcastic.
कुबट kubaṭa adj. inv. musty, moldy.
कुबड kubaḍa n. hump on the back.
कुबेर kubēra m. 1. the god of wealth. 2. a very wealthy man.
कुभांड kubhāṇḍa n. false accusation. ० रचणे to accuse falsely.
कुंभार kumbhāra m. 1. potter. 2. the potter caste cluster.
कुमार kumāra m. 1. a young boy. 2. descriptive title preceding a boy's name.
कुमारिका kumārikā f. a young girl, virgin.
कुमारी kumārī f. 1. a young girl, virgin. 2. descriptive title preceding a girl's name.
कुरतडणे kurataḍaṇē v.t. to gnaw, pick at.
कुरापत kurāpata , काढणे kāḍhaṇē to provoke.
कुलगुरू kulagurū m. vice-chancellor of a university.
कुलूप kulūpa n. lock. ० लावणे to lock.
कुवत kuvata f.(i) strength, ability, capability.
कुशल kuśala adj. inv. skilled, skillful.
कुसकरणे kusakaraṇē v.t. to crush, crumble.
कूस kūsa f.(i) side of the body. क्षच्या कुशीत in X's arms.
कूळ kūḷa n. 1. family. 2. tenant farmer.
कृती kṛtī f. 1. action. ० करणे to take action. 2. recipe.
कृत्य kṛtya n. action. ० करणे to perform an action.
कृत्रिम kṛtrima adj. inv. artificial, synthene.
कृपा kṛpā f. favor, kindness. क्षच्या कृपेने thanks to X. ० करणे to be kind. do a favor.
कृश kṛśa adj. inv. thin, slender.
कृष्ण kṛṣṇa m. a god (one of the incarnations of Vishnu). He is often pictured as a cowherd. adj. inv. black, dark.
केकटणे kēkaṭaṇē v.t. to howl, yell.
केर kēra m. rubbish. ० काढणे to sweep.
केरवारा kēravārā , करणे karaṇē to sweep, clean.
केवढे kēvaḍhē adj. how much, how big.
केशरी kēśarī adj. inv. orange, saffron-colored.
केशवपन kēśavapana n. shaving of the head (esp. of a widow).
केस kēsa m. 1. a hair. 2. (in pl.) hair.
केसर kēsara m. pl. 1. the reproductive organs of a flower. 2. fiber.

केळवण kēḷavaṇa n. ceremonial meal before a wedding given by: (1) bride's or bridegroom's parents to friends and relatives (2) bride's or bridegroom's parents, friends and relatives to the bride's or bridegroom's family. In the second case wedding gifts to the parents are often given on this occasion.
कैकाडी kaikāḍī m. a semi-tribal community formerly listed as one of the criminal tribes.
कैवार kaivāra , घेणे ghēṇē to align oneself with one side in a dispute.
कोकण kōkaṇa n. the Konkan (the coastal belt of Maharashtra).
कोकलणे kōkalaṇē v.i. to cry loudly.
कोटी kōṭī f. 1. pun. 2. ten million (10,000,000)
कोठडी kōṭhaḍī f. storeroom. अंधार dungeon.
कोंडणे kōṇḍaṇē v.t. to shut in, confine. श्वास 0 to hold one's breath, stifle.
कोंडा kōṇḍā m. bran, husk of grain.
कोतवाल kōtavāla m. 1. village watchman. 2. messenger in the revenue department 3. formerly a police officer.
कोते kōtē adj. deficient, hence, narrow (of mental attitude), thin (of a voice).
कोंदट kōndaṭa adj. inv. close, confined, stuffy.
कोंदण kōndaṇa n. setting of a gem.
कोंबणे kōmbaṇē v.t. to cram in.
कोमल kōmala adj. inv. gentle, soft.
कोमेजणे kōmējaṇē v.i. to wither, droop.
कोरडवाहू kōraḍavāhū adj. inv. unirrigated, rainfed.
कोरणे kōraṇē v.t. 1. to carve, engrave. 2. to pick at.
कोरीव kōrīva adj. inv. 1. engraved. 2. fine-drawn.
कोरे kōrē adj. 1. blank. 2. black (as coffee, tea, etc).
कोलमडणे kōlamaḍaṇē v.i. to trip, stumble.
कोलांटी kōlāṇṭī f. somersault. ० मारणे to somersault.
कोल्हाटी kōlhāṭī m. tumbler and acrobat.
कोवळे kōvaḷē adj. 1. tender. 2. mild, pale (as sunlight).
कोश kōśa m. 1. cocoon. 2. treasury. 3. dictionary.
कोष्टी kōṣṭī m. 1. weaver. 2. the weaver caste-cluster.
कोस kōsa m. a measure of distance. The term is not used with exactness but can be taken to mean approximately two and one half miles.
कोसळणे kōsaḷaṇē v.i. to crash down, collapse.
कोळ kōḷa m. pulp, thick juice (as of tamarind).
कोळसा kōḷasā m. 1. coal, charcoal. 2. piece of coal, charcoal.
कोळी kōḷī m. 1. fisherman. 2. a caste of west-coast sea-fishermen. 3. semi-tribal community of inland fishermen and water carriers, formerly listed as a criminal tribe. 4. spider.
कौतुक kautuka n. making much of.
कौल kaula n. roof tile. m. response to a petition.
कौलारू kaulārū adj. inv. having a tiled roof.
क्रमप्राप्त kramaprāpta adv. inevitable in the course of events.
क्रमशः kramaśaḥ adv. in serial order, gradually.
क्रांतिकारक krāntikāraka m., adj. inv. revolutionary.
क्रिया kriyā f. 1. action, activity, process. 2. religious rite.
क्लिष्ट kliṣṭa adj. inv. difficult, complicated.
खंगणे khaṅgaṇē v.i. to decline in health.
खचणे khacaṇē v.i. 1. to be undermined. 2. to lose one's morale.
खजिना khajinā m. treasure house, treasury.
खटकणे khaṭakaṇē v.i. (N-la impers.) to bother.

खराब kharāba adj. inv. bad, spoiled.
